snippet.textDisplay: They kinda sweetened the scene between Gen and Lara Jean. In the books, it's not such a comfortable scene. Gen tells LJ why she hated her (in the books, Peter and LJ kissed out of their own will and not because of the game, and Gen had liked Peter at that time and scene them kissing) and revealed that she had hated LJ for years even when she pretended to be her friend. LJ apologised to her and asked if they could be friends again, but Gen declines the offer. This conversation however gives LJ some closure. The book basically ends with LJ accepting that some people are not meant to be in your life forever, and her saying goodbye and moving on. Honestly, it would have been better if they put that in the movie instead of the randomly-becoming-friends-after-hating-each-other-for-years.

snippet.textDisplay: WAIT.... let’s discuss the notion that LJ was using PK in the first movie because I think you’re too hard on her. Just because Peter started liking her at some point, doesn’t change the fact that LJ thought this was still a show for Gen. I wouldn’t have gotten my hopes up either considering that he let Gen take LJ’s Hair tie, and spent the night in Gen’s room... after insinuating that he wanted to sit by LJ on the bus and spend time with her... and (New info) was waiting for Gen in the hot tub and lied about not knowing that Gen posted the video. I’d think he was full of it too. This movie on the other hand, I was more irritated in the John A. situation. He was dragged into her mess for no reason. She lead him on. Also, the way she even had doubts about Peter just by getting a letter from a guy she hadn’t seen in 5 years just shows her dedication to her relationship (which was real hypocritical given that she was always worried about whether PK was thinking of another girl).
